%N A394336 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1 + 1/(p^6 - p^4)).
%C A394336 The asymptotic mean of the number of cubefull divisors of the greatest common divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random.
%C A394336 In general, the asymptotic mean of the number of k-full divisors (k-full numbers are numbers whose prime factorization has no exponent that is smaller than k) of the greatest common divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is Product_{p prime} (1 + 1/(p^(2*k) - p^(2*k-2))).
%F A394336 Equals lim_{m->oo} (1/m^2) * Sum_{i,j=1..m} A190867(gcd(i, j)).
%F A394336 Equals zeta(2) * Product_{p prime} (1- 1/p^2 + 1/p^6) =  A013661 * A393649.
%e A394336 1.022486596136980366191611409373598359445927292726914...
%o A394336 (PARI) prodeulerrat(1 + 1/(p^6 - p^4))
%Y A394336 Cf. A013661, A036966, A190867, A393649, A394335.
